rounds.response:
I'm in the Big Blind with an off-suit 3-7, one of the worst starting hands in Hold'em. Since the Small Blind has already put in his 20-chip raise and it's now heads-up, I only have to call an additional 10 chips (from 10 to 20) to see the pot that is already 30 chips. Against a random single opponent, 10 chips into a 30-chip pot is 3-to-1; I need ~25% equity to justify a call. 3-7 offsuit does have slightly more than 25% equity against a wide heads-up range. So, calling the minimum is marginally +EV here, and folding would give away 10 chips. I'll complete the call.

[Call]
